They are both compile-time operations.

Type erasure is translation from generic Java source code back into regular Java code (removes `T`, `A` and any other paramterized types).

Type inference can happen when a generic method is invoked or when a generic type object is created. For example, if you 

    class Box&lt;T&gt; {
        ...
    }

Then when you write

