@MarkWood in my experience clunky testing experiences are generally a sign of some design flaw.  

IRL if you are testing constructors your code is probably screaming at you for a factory or some dependency injection.  If you follow typical design patterns for those two cases your code becomes much easier to test and to work with in general.

